
TEACHER SUBSTITUTION MANAGEMENT SYSTEM
Version 1.0


DESCRIPTION:
This is a web-based application designed to help school administration
quickly identify available teachers for substitution when a teacher is absent.

SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS:
- Any modern web browser (Chrome, Edge, Firefox)
- No internet connection required after initial load
- No software installation required

HOW TO USE:
1. Open the file "index.html" in your web browser
2. Upload the Excel timetable files for each class (Step 1)
   - Supported format:.xlsx or.xls
   - Timetable structure: Days in columns, Periods in rows
   - Cell format: "Subject (Teacher Name)"
3. Select Day, enter Period Number, and enter Absent Teacher Name (Step 2)
4. Click "Generate Available Teachers List"
5. The system will display all teachers who are free in that period

FEATURES:
- Case-insensitive search: Accepts any capitalization for names
- Multi-class support: Checks across all uploaded timetables
- Instant results: No manual checking required
- Print-friendly: Results can be printed directly from browser

DATA PRIVACY:
- All data processing happens locally in your browser
- No data is uploaded to any server
- Timetable files remain on your computer

